                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1237: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-02T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 2, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 2—10:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. I explained verbally to the Minister for Foreign Affairs the United States
                    Government’s position in respect to Palestine as suggested <pb facs="0988"
                        n="980" xml:id="pg_980"/> in the Department’s telegram No. 21, October 27, 9
                    p.m. [<hi rend="italic">7 p.m.</hi>]<note n="3" xml:id="d804fn3">See footnote
                        97, <ref target="#pg_975">p. 975</ref>.</note> He replied as follows. He
                    would be glad to secure the support of the United States for the Palestine Arab
                    cause in the present crisis, but if not possible he would of course hope that
                    such support would not be accorded to the Jews, and that the United States
                    Government would not intervene with the British Government and adversely
                    influence the decision which he believes it is about to make. He would be
                    satisfied he said to have the American policy, as recently defined by the
                    Secretary of State, remain the same, no more no less.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
